<paragraph id="E8403669FFB3FFCFFE0B1C4286C5B461" blockId="36.[402,913,1615,1642]" box="[402,913,1615,1642]" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">
<heading id="B3088105FFB3FFCFFE0B1C4286C5B461" box="[402,913,1615,1642]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB3FFCFFE0B1C4286C5B461" authority="(Cranston, 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Cranston" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[402,913,1615,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bromelicola">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB3FFCFFE0B1C4287EAB461" bold="true" box="[402,702,1615,1642]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">Tanytarsus bromelicola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB3FFCFFD571C4286DCB461" author="Cranston PS" box="[718,904,1615,1642]" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" pagination="617 - 622" refId="ref23777" refString="Cranston PS. 2007. A new species for a bromeliad phytotelm-dwelling Tanytarsus (Diptera: Chironomidae). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 100 (5): 617 - 622. doi: 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2007) 100 [617: ANSFAB] 2.0. CO; 2." type="journal article" year="2007">Cranston, 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB3FFCFFF591C8881D7B495" blockId="36.[160,1155,1669,1728]" box="[192,1155,1669,1694]" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">This chironomid is a predator and was found in ornamental bromeliad phytotelmata in</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A0E565E2FFB3FFCEFF391CAA86FAB418" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="836" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" type="description">
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB3FFCEFF391CAA85A7B339" blockId="36.[160,1155,1669,1728]" lastBlockId="37.[160,1156,142,306]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="836" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">
Mahogany Run on St. Thomas. This is the only species in the genus known from bromeliads, and is reported from 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB2FFCEFDB81A8387F7B2AC" box="[545,675,142,167]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
and Florida (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFCA21A8386B5B2AC" author="Cranston PS" box="[827,993,142,167]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="617 - 622" refId="ref23777" refString="Cranston PS. 2007. A new species for a bromeliad phytotelm-dwelling Tanytarsus (Diptera: Chironomidae). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 100 (5): 617 - 622. doi: 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2007) 100 [617: ANSFAB] 2.0. CO; 2." type="journal article" year="2007">Cranston 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFC6F1A8381D0B2AC" author="Miller AC" box="[1014,1156,142,167]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="391 - 396" refId="ref27369" refString="Miller AC. 1971. Observations on the Chironomidae (Diptera) inhabiting the leaf axils of two species of Bromeliaceae on St. John, US Virgin Islands. Can Entomol. 103 (3): 391 - 396. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 103391 - 3." type="journal article" year="1971">Miller (1971)</bibRefCitation>
identified a chironomid from St. John bromeliads as possibly 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFC111ABC8153B2C1" authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1915" box="[904,1031,177,202]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFC111ABC8153B2C1" box="[904,1031,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">T. confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFF391AD98407B2E6" author="Cranston PS" box="[160,339,212,237]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="617 - 622" refId="ref23777" refString="Cranston PS. 2007. A new species for a bromeliad phytotelm-dwelling Tanytarsus (Diptera: Chironomidae). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 100 (5): 617 - 622. doi: 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2007) 100 [617: ANSFAB] 2.0. CO; 2." type="journal article" year="2007">Cranston (2007)</bibRefCitation>
argues the identification was likely mistaken and those specimens were 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF391AFB846EB304" baseAuthorityName="Cranston" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[160,314,246,271]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bromelicola">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF391AFB846EB304" box="[160,314,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">T. bromelicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As such, this is the first confirmed record of this species from the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB2FFCEFBD81AFB85BBB339" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF391B5384BFB373" blockId="37.[160,1155,350,479]" box="[160,491,350,376]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF391B5384BFB373" bold="true" box="[160,491,350,376]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Odontomyia 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFEA11B538415B373" bold="true" box="[312,321,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">/</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFEDB1B5384B4B373" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1914" box="[322,480,350,376]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Hedriodiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hedriodiscus</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFE461B5384BFB373" bold="true" box="[479,491,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">?</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF391B8C86B5B3D4" blockId="37.[160,1155,350,479]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Little is known about the 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFE7B1B8C872AB391" box="[482,638,385,410]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Stratiomyidae</taxonomicName>
of the Caribbean. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFCF01B8C815CB391" author="Curran CH" box="[873,1032,385,410]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran (1928)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF391BA9843AB3B6" authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1928" box="[160,366,420,445]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Nemotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomae">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF391BA9843AB3B6" box="[160,366,420,445]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Nemotelus thomae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from saline pools on St. Thomas. We collected early instar stratiomyid larvae from freshwater in Bolongo pond, from dense marginal vegetation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF3918068412B02E" blockId="37.[160,1155,523,653]" box="[160,326,523,549]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF3918068412B02E" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1835" box="[160,326,523,549]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF3918068412B02E" bold="true" box="[160,326,523,549]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Cecidomyidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF3918228457B086" blockId="37.[160,1155,523,653]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Unidentified larvae of this family were found on St. Thomas at the University of the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB2FFCEFBD8182285B8B061" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
in moss clumps in a concrete drainage behind the Classroom Administration Building.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF3918B48471B0D8" blockId="37.[160,1156,697,1138]" box="[160,293,697,723]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF3918B48471B0D8" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1837" box="[160,293,697,723]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF3918B48471B0D8" bold="true" box="[160,293,697,723]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Ephydridae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF3918D18420B679" blockId="37.[160,1156,697,1138]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Unidentified larvae from the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFDFD18D187B7B0FE" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1837" box="[612,739,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ephydrinae">Ephydrinae</taxonomicName>
were found in bromeliads from the Yacht Haven Grande Marina. Species in this family known from the US Virgin Islands, include 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF64192F873EB130" authority="Loew, 1878" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1878" box="[253,618,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Paralimna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF64192F848FB130" box="[253,475,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Paralimna decipiens</emphasis>
Loew, 1878
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFDEE192F86C9B130" authority="Williston, 1896" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1896" box="[631,925,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Ranatra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFDEE192F87BEB130" box="[631,746,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">P. obscura</emphasis>
Williston, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFC32192F846AB156" authority="Cresson, 1941" authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discocerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFC32192F81D7B130" box="[939,1155,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discocerina flavipes</emphasis>
Cresson, 1941
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFED01949878FB156" authority="(Fallen, 1813)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[329,731,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discocerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurella">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFED01949876FB156" box="[329,571,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discocerina obscurella</emphasis>
(Fall√©n, 1813)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFD7F194981D4B156" authority="(Loew, 1862)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[742,1152,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Cressonomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculata">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFD7F194986B3B156" box="[742,999,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Cressonomyia aciculata</emphasis>
(Loew, 1862)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF39196A8741B18B" authority="Williston, 1896" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1896" box="[160,533,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF39196A840AB18B" box="[160,350,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discomyza dubia</emphasis>
Williston, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFDBD196A8174B18B" authority="(Wiedemann, 1824)" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[548,1056,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculipennis">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFDBD196A8660B18B" box="[548,820,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discomyza maculipennis</emphasis>
(Wiedemann, 1824)
