<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFD5719A186CAB1CE" author="Mathis WN &amp; Rodrigues FDA Jr. &amp; Couri MS" box="[718,926,940,965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="752 - 770" refId="ref27000" refString="Mathis WN, Rodrigues FDA Jr., Couri MS. 2016. Family Ephydridae. Zootaxa. 4122 (1): 752 - 770. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4122.1.64." type="journal article" year="2016">Mathis et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFC2C19A1842EB1E3" authority="(Wiedemann, 1830)" authorityName="Ale-Rocha and Mathis" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Paralimna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomae">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFC2C19A181D7B1CE" box="[949,1155,940,965]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Paralimna thomae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFF3F19C28427B1E3" author="Wiedemann CRW" box="[166,371,975,1000]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" refId="ref31761" refString="Wiedemann CRW. 1830. Aussereuropaische zweiflugelige Insecten, Vol. 2. Hamm (GER): Schulz; p. 648." type="journal volume" year="1830">Wiedemann, 1830</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from St. Thomas (as 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFCE419C28165B1E3" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[893,1073,975,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Ephydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomae">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFCE419C28165B1E3" box="[893,1073,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Ephydra thomae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and is the most widespread member of the genus in the Americas (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFCDD19FC8122B601" author="Ale-Rocha R &amp; Mathis WN" box="[836,1142,1009,1034]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22105" refString="Ale-Rocha R, Mathis WN. 2015. A revision of the New World species of Paralimna Loew (Diptera: Ephydridae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 643: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="2015">Ale-Rocha and Mathis 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Several other 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFEA71E1984E9B626" authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1837" box="[318,445,1044,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ephydridae</taxonomicName>
are known from Puerto Rico and could also occur in the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB2FFCEFBD61E1981D7B626" box="[1103,1155,1044,1069]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">USVI</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFF3F1E3A8461B65B" author="Curran CH" box="[166,309,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran 1928</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFEDC1E3A8484B65B" author="Barber HG" box="[325,464,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="264 - 441" refId="ref22283" refString="Barber HG. 1939. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: Hemiptera-Heteroptera (excepting the Miridae and Corixidae). Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 14: 264 - 441." type="journal article" year="1939">Barber 1939</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFE781E3A867BB65B" author="Mathis WN &amp; Zatwarnicki T" box="[481,815,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref27035" refString="Mathis WN, Zatwarnicki T. 2012. A revision of the new world species of Polytrichophora Cresson and Facitrichophora, new genus (Diptera, Ephydridae). ZooKeys. 231: 1 - 116. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 231.3687." type="journal article" year="2012">Mathis and Zatwarnicki 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFCD91E3A812AB65B" author="Ale-Rocha R &amp; Mathis WN" box="[832,1150,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22105" refString="Ale-Rocha R, Mathis WN. 2015. A revision of the New World species of Paralimna Loew (Diptera: Ephydridae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 643: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="2015">Ale-Rocha and Mathis 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFF391E548433B679" author="Mathis WN &amp; Rodrigues FDA Jr. &amp; Couri MS" box="[160,359,1113,1138]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="752 - 770" refId="ref27000" refString="Mathis WN, Rodrigues FDA Jr., Couri MS. 2016. Family Ephydridae. Zootaxa. 4122 (1): 752 - 770. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4122.1.64." type="journal article" year="2016">Mathis et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF391E938442B6B3" blockId="37.[160,1156,1182,1555]" box="[160,278,1182,1208]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF391E938442B6B3" box="[160,278,1182,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF391E938442B6B3" bold="true" box="[160,278,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Syrphidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF391ECF847BB7A0" blockId="37.[160,1156,1182,1555]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Unidentified larvae were found on St. Thomas in brackish pools with decomposing vegetation in the mangroves at Magens Beach and Red Hook. A freshwater form very similar to 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFE961F0A840EB72B" box="[271,346,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Erstalis</emphasis>
sp. was encountered in the dense, rotting vegetation of an embayment part of a small ghut at Raphune Hill (which also had evidence of septic contamination). 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFF391F41846CB76E" author="Curran CH" box="[160,312,1356,1381]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran (1928)</bibRefCitation>
reported two species of 
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFDD41F4187CCB76E" box="[589,664,1356,1381]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Erstalis</emphasis>
from St. Thomas. Other syrphid larvae were found in 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFE8C1F6284B1B783" box="[277,485,1391,1416]" class="Liliopsida" family="Heliconiaceae" genus="Heliconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caribaea">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFE8C1F6284B1B783" box="[277,485,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Heliconia caribaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFDB51F628649B783" box="[556,797,1391,1416]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Billbergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyramidalis">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFDB51F628649B783" box="[556,797,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Billbergia pyramidalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
phytotelmata at the Etelman Observatory.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FFB2FFCEFF591FB986FAB418" blockId="37.[160,1156,1182,1555]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFF591FB9840DB7C6" author="Curran CH" box="[192,345,1460,1485]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran (1928)</bibRefCitation>
reported several syrphid species from Puerto Rico and the 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FFB2FFCEFC6C1FB98178B7C6" box="[1013,1068,1460,1485]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">USVI</collectingCountry>
, including 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFF551FDA870BB7FB" authority="Wiedemann, 1830" authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[204,607,1495,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Palpada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifrons">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFF551FDA84DFB7FB" box="[204,395,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Palpada albifrons</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFE0A1FDA870BB7FB" author="Wiedemann CRW" box="[403,607,1495,1520]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" refId="ref31761" refString="Wiedemann CRW. 1830. Aussereuropaische zweiflugelige Insecten, Vol. 2. Hamm (GER): Schulz; p. 648." type="journal volume" year="1830">Wiedemann, 1830</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFFB2FFCEFD001FDA8167B7FB" authority="(Walker, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[665,1075,1495,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Meromacrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laconicus">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFFB2FFCEFD001FDA86D8B7FB" box="[665,908,1495,1520]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Meromacrus laconicus</emphasis>
(Walker, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
(a tree hole species) from St. Thomas (
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFE671FF7878AB418" author="van Doesburg PH" box="[510,734,1530,1555]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="90 - 101" refId="ref31261" refString="van Doesburg PH. 1970. Records of Syrphidae (Diptera) from the Lesser Antilles. Stud Fauna Curacao Carib Isl. 34: 90 - 101." type="journal article" year="1970">Van Doesburg 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FFB2FFCEFD721FF786F6B418" author="Thompson FC" box="[747,930,1530,1555]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 200" refId="ref30802" refString="Thompson FC. 1981. The flower flies of the West Indies (Diptera: Syrphidae). Mem Entomol Soc Wash. 9: 1 - 200." type="journal article" year="1981">Thompson 1981</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
